vectorData.altText: 8. Identify the layer indicated by the letter A. Be specific.

Cells here undergo keratinization, in which the proteins of the keratohyalin granules associate with the bundles of keratin intermediate filaments to form larger masses of proteins that pack the cytoplasm.
Also, lamellar granules release their lipid contents through exocytosis into the intercellular space. By packing the space between cells with lipid (like mortar packed between bricks), this contributes to the epidermal water barrier.
Keratinocytes lose their organelles and die in this layer as they move into the s. corneum.
That's right! Stratum granulosum contains cells undergoing keratinization. Dark-staining keratohyalin granules fill the cytoplasm in this layer.
